name: Da Vinci's Salvator Mundi by Zaam
description: Salvator Mundi (Latin for ''Savior of the World'') is a painting attributed in whole or in part to the Italian High Renaissance artist Leonardo da Vinci, dated to c. 1499–1510.   This particular piece is my version of a savior of the world or rather saviors with repetition of false apostles that we have seen in history.
